1
00:00:02,169 --> 00:00:04,338
Narrator: Now with
a new set of wheels,

2
00:00:04,371 --> 00:00:06,640
jojo and crew
head north from varanasi

3
00:00:06,673 --> 00:00:09,142
to the nation of Pakistan.

4
00:00:10,644 --> 00:00:13,147
Kakyoin: We’re about to hit
the indo-Pakistani border.

5
00:00:13,180 --> 00:00:15,382
I guess it’s time
to say goodbye to India.

6
00:00:15,415 --> 00:00:17,183
Joseph: You know,
I had mixed feelings

7
00:00:17,217 --> 00:00:20,387
about the country at first,
but now I actually kind of miss

8
00:00:20,420 --> 00:00:22,155
the hustle and bustle
of Calcutta

9
00:00:22,189 --> 00:00:24,425
and frenetic chaos
of the Ganges.

10
00:00:24,458 --> 00:00:26,160
( Jotaro scoffs )

11
00:00:26,193 --> 00:00:29,196
Polnareff: I’ll be coming
back again one of these days.

12
00:00:29,229 --> 00:00:32,365
I owe it to avdol
to give him a proper burial.

13
00:00:32,399 --> 00:00:33,567
( Jotaro sighs )

14
00:00:33,600 --> 00:00:34,968
( Joseph sighs )

15
00:00:35,002 --> 00:00:36,303
( Kakyoin sighs )

16
00:00:36,336 --> 00:00:38,371
Mr. Avdol.

17
00:00:38,405 --> 00:00:40,307
Polnareff: The road’s
getting narrower.

18
00:00:40,340 --> 00:00:41,374
Kakyoin: Hmm?

19
00:00:45,179 --> 00:00:47,214
( Car engine revs )

20
00:00:47,247 --> 00:00:48,482
( Polnareff coughs )

21
00:00:48,515 --> 00:00:50,217
Quit driving so slow, idiot!

22
00:00:50,250 --> 00:00:51,351
Out of the way!

23
00:00:51,385 --> 00:00:52,686
I’m gonna pass the guy.

24
00:00:57,491 --> 00:00:59,493
Kakyoin: Polnareff, calm down.

25
00:00:59,526 --> 00:01:00,594
( Polnareff laughs )

26
00:01:00,627 --> 00:01:02,629
This four-wheel drive is great.

27
00:01:02,663 --> 00:01:04,698
Joseph: You know,
that crazy maneuver of yours

28
00:01:04,731 --> 00:01:06,533
might have just damaged
that poor car.

29
00:01:06,567 --> 00:01:08,302
Polnareff: Yeah. Your point?

30
00:01:08,335 --> 00:01:11,505
Joseph: I’m saying we
don’t need any more trouble now.

31
00:01:11,538 --> 00:01:14,274
I’m wanted because of
what happened in varanasi.

32
00:01:14,308 --> 00:01:17,111
I’d like to get
across the border in one piece.

33
00:01:19,313 --> 00:01:20,381
( Polnareff gasps )

34
00:01:21,815 --> 00:01:23,250
( All grunt )

35
00:01:23,283 --> 00:01:25,018
Kakyoin: What’s up?
Why’d you stop?

36
00:01:25,052 --> 00:01:27,488
Joseph: I told you.
A crash could be disastrous.

37
00:01:27,521 --> 00:01:30,691
Polnareff: I know that.
Just look who’s standing there.

38
00:01:30,724 --> 00:01:32,726
( Anne humming a tune )

39
00:01:34,528 --> 00:01:36,163
( Jotaro scoffs )

40
00:01:36,196 --> 00:01:38,098
Good freakin’ grief.

41
00:01:38,131 --> 00:01:40,734
Anne: Hey.
Long time no see, guys.

42
00:01:40,767 --> 00:01:42,469
Got room for one more?

43
00:01:42,503 --> 00:01:45,172
( All gasp, stammer )

44
00:01:52,145 --> 00:01:54,447
( Car engine revving )

45
00:01:57,818 --> 00:01:59,820
♪

46
00:02:07,160 --> 00:02:09,162
( Singing in Japanese )

47
00:02:43,864 --> 00:02:45,866
Anne: I mean, come on.
I’m a girl.

48
00:02:45,899 --> 00:02:48,735
Soon i’ll be doing girl things
like wearing a bra

49
00:02:48,769 --> 00:02:51,372
and doing my nails
to get the attention of boys.

50
00:02:51,405 --> 00:02:52,740
I’d look pathetic

51
00:02:52,773 --> 00:02:55,309
wandering around the world
when i’m that age.

52
00:02:55,342 --> 00:02:58,879
This is the only chance I have
to be free and see the world.

53
00:02:58,912 --> 00:02:59,880
Polnareff: Mm.

54
00:02:59,913 --> 00:03:01,882
Anne: Know what I mean?

55
00:03:01,915 --> 00:03:05,152
Look, I feel bad
for lying about going to see

56
00:03:05,185 --> 00:03:08,488
my dad in Singapore, but let’s
just forget about that.

57
00:03:08,522 --> 00:03:10,391
( Car horn honking )

58
00:03:10,424 --> 00:03:12,526
Jotaro: Hey,
it’s that car we passed.

59
00:03:12,559 --> 00:03:14,394
Looks like he’s in a hurry.

60
00:03:14,428 --> 00:03:15,896
Joseph: Let ’em pass,
okay, polnareff?

61
00:03:15,929 --> 00:03:17,364
Polnareff: Yeah.

62
00:03:23,904 --> 00:03:26,607
( Car engine revs )

63
00:03:31,245 --> 00:03:33,180
Polnareff: What the hell?

64
00:03:33,213 --> 00:03:34,648
( All coughing )

65
00:03:34,681 --> 00:03:36,550
Polnareff:
What’s he trying to do?

66
00:03:36,583 --> 00:03:37,784
I let you pass.

67
00:03:37,818 --> 00:03:39,586
Now hurry up, and go already!

68
00:03:43,390 --> 00:03:45,659
Kakyoin: He’s probably angry
about your maneuver,

69
00:03:45,692 --> 00:03:47,394
and these are
the consequences.

70
00:03:47,427 --> 00:03:50,430
Jotaro: So did you get a look
at the driver’s face?

71
00:03:50,464 --> 00:03:53,167
Polnareff: No. The windows
were covered in thick dust.

72
00:03:53,200 --> 00:03:54,535
Couldn’t see a thing.

73
00:03:54,568 --> 00:03:55,803
Jotaro: Neither could I.

74
00:03:55,836 --> 00:03:57,771
Couldn’t be.

75
00:03:57,804 --> 00:03:59,806
Joseph: Be very careful,
polnareff.

76
00:04:00,807 --> 00:04:01,975
Polnareff: Hmm?

77
00:04:04,211 --> 00:04:06,447
Heh. Now he’s wants me to pass.

78
00:04:06,480 --> 00:04:07,881
Looks like the fool’s realized

79
00:04:07,915 --> 00:04:09,950
how shitty
that piece of junk is.

80
00:04:09,983 --> 00:04:12,752
You should have stayed behind me
the first place, dumb-ass.

81
00:04:12,786 --> 00:04:14,454
Comin’ through!

82
00:04:15,789 --> 00:04:16,857
( Gasps )

83
00:04:16,890 --> 00:04:18,859
- What?!
- ( Truck horn honks )

84
00:04:18,892 --> 00:04:20,460
( Polnareff screams )

85
00:04:20,494 --> 00:04:21,695
Where’d that come from?!

86
00:04:21,728 --> 00:04:23,296
Kakyoin: No use. Hold on.

87
00:04:25,232 --> 00:04:26,700
Jotaro: Star platinum!

88
00:04:32,005 --> 00:04:33,874
Polnareff: That was close.

89
00:04:33,907 --> 00:04:36,777
( Sighs ) If it weren’t
for star platinum’s power,

90
00:04:36,810 --> 00:04:39,880
we would have been crushed
beneath that like a tin can.

91
00:04:39,913 --> 00:04:42,883
Joseph: He’s gone.
Where did that blasted car go?

92
00:04:42,916 --> 00:04:45,285
Jotaro: Looks like
it just kept going.

93
00:04:45,319 --> 00:04:50,224
I think the driver could have
been one of the stand users.

94
00:04:50,257 --> 00:04:53,894
Then again, it could have
just been some sick bastard.

95
00:04:53,927 --> 00:04:56,263
Of course
he’s one of dio’s lackeys.

96
00:04:56,296 --> 00:04:58,431
We were almost roadkill,
for god’s sake.

97
00:04:58,465 --> 00:05:01,568
Kakyoin: Then why didn’t he
simply attack us with his stand

98
00:05:01,602 --> 00:05:02,803
when he had the chance?

99
00:05:02,836 --> 00:05:04,504
- ( Car engine starts )
- Joseph: Anyway,

100
00:05:04,538 --> 00:05:07,274
we’ve gotta keep heading
to Pakistan. Be on guard.

101
00:05:07,307 --> 00:05:10,677
If someone comes after us again,
we’ll make ’em eat our dust.

102
00:05:10,711 --> 00:05:11,946
Polnareff: Damn straight.

103
00:05:11,979 --> 00:05:14,415
Kakyoin: What should we do
about that truck?

104
00:05:14,448 --> 00:05:17,518
Star platinum left it a wreck.
It won’t be going anywhere.

105
00:05:17,551 --> 00:05:18,519
Jotaro: That’s easy.

106
00:05:18,552 --> 00:05:20,421
We pretend we never saw it.

107
00:05:20,454 --> 00:05:21,422
Let’s get going.

108
00:05:21,455 --> 00:05:22,790
♪

109
00:05:22,823 --> 00:05:25,326
Anne: He’s so cool.

110
00:05:35,869 --> 00:05:37,771
( Car engine revving )

111
00:05:49,683 --> 00:05:51,785
Joseph: A roadside tea stand.

112
00:05:54,021 --> 00:05:56,590
A break would do us some good.

113
00:05:56,623 --> 00:05:58,024
If we take our time,

114
00:05:58,058 --> 00:06:00,594
we may avoid running into
that crazy driver.

115
00:06:00,627 --> 00:06:02,596
♪

116
00:06:09,436 --> 00:06:11,405
( Rollers squeaking )

117
00:06:11,438 --> 00:06:13,307
Joseph: What is that stuff?

118
00:06:13,340 --> 00:06:15,375
Shopkeeper:
Fresh sugar-cane juice.

119
00:06:16,643 --> 00:06:18,445
Care for a glass?

120
00:06:18,478 --> 00:06:20,747
Joseph sure. Why not?

121
00:06:23,383 --> 00:06:24,451
Mm.

122
00:06:24,484 --> 00:06:25,618
What?!

123
00:06:25,652 --> 00:06:26,720
( Gasps )

124
00:06:26,753 --> 00:06:27,721
( Others gasp )

125
00:06:27,754 --> 00:06:28,955
Polnareff: I-it’s him.

126
00:06:28,989 --> 00:06:30,524
That car’s here!

127
00:06:40,901 --> 00:06:42,936
Joseph: Hey, tell me something.

128
00:06:42,970 --> 00:06:45,606
Who’s the owner of that car
parked over there?

129
00:06:45,639 --> 00:06:47,107
Come on. Spill it!

130
00:06:47,140 --> 00:06:49,342
Shopkeeper:
Uh, i’m not sure, sir.

131
00:06:49,376 --> 00:06:52,512
To be honest, sir,
I didn’t notice it there.

132
00:06:52,546 --> 00:06:53,814
Kakyoin: Our driver
isn’t just going

133
00:06:53,847 --> 00:06:55,349
to come out and announce it.

134
00:06:55,382 --> 00:06:56,583
Polnareff: He’s messing with us.

135
00:06:56,617 --> 00:06:58,419
Joseph: Yeah.
Then, I guess this leaves us

136
00:06:58,452 --> 00:07:00,721
with only one option,
right, jotaro?

137
00:07:00,754 --> 00:07:01,722
Jotaro: Yeah.

138
00:07:01,755 --> 00:07:03,557
Poor innocent bastards.

139
00:07:03,590 --> 00:07:04,825
Customers: Huh?

140
00:07:04,858 --> 00:07:07,060
Jotaro: We’ll just
beat them all down.

141
00:07:07,094 --> 00:07:08,062
( Kakyoin gasps )

142
00:07:08,095 --> 00:07:09,597
( Customer grunting )

143
00:07:09,630 --> 00:07:12,700
Kakyoin: Hey, jotaro,
this is crazy.

144
00:07:12,733 --> 00:07:14,735
Mr. Joestar, not you, too!

145
00:07:14,768 --> 00:07:17,437
Polnareff: Pretty suspicious mug
you got there. Was it you?

146
00:07:17,471 --> 00:07:18,639
Customer #2: Wha?! Not me!

147
00:07:18,672 --> 00:07:19,773
( Car door closes )

148
00:07:19,806 --> 00:07:20,807
- All: Huh?
- ( Car engine revving )

149
00:07:28,749 --> 00:07:29,950
Polnareff: That slippery bastard

150
00:07:29,983 --> 00:07:32,519
just played the lot of us,
didn’t he?

151
00:07:32,553 --> 00:07:34,889
Joseph: Damn it.
Did anyone see his face?

152
00:07:34,922 --> 00:07:38,459
Kakyoin: No.
What is he trying to do?

153
00:07:38,492 --> 00:07:40,828
He could be
just some madman with a car,

154
00:07:40,861 --> 00:07:42,896
or he could be
trying to kill us.

155
00:07:42,930 --> 00:07:43,998
( Polnareff growls )

156
00:07:44,031 --> 00:07:45,799
We need
to take care of this crap.

157
00:07:45,833 --> 00:07:48,703
I won’t rest until I catch him
and get to the bottom of this.

158
00:07:49,770 --> 00:07:51,005
Not to mention
we owe him payback

159
00:07:51,038 --> 00:07:53,541
for the truck that
almost hit us earlier.

160
00:07:54,741 --> 00:07:56,743
( Men gasping )

161
00:07:57,845 --> 00:07:59,847
♪

162
00:08:01,481 --> 00:08:03,650
( Tires skidding )

163
00:08:05,552 --> 00:08:07,721
( Car engine revs )

164
00:08:07,754 --> 00:08:09,823
Polnareff: Damn it.
For a piece of shit,

165
00:08:09,857 --> 00:08:11,992
that car can
really get up and go.

166
00:08:12,025 --> 00:08:14,027
♪

167
00:08:24,571 --> 00:08:26,840
Kakyoin: That’s strange.
According to the map,

168
00:08:26,874 --> 00:08:30,077
we should be running parallel
with train tracks or something.

169
00:08:30,110 --> 00:08:33,146
Polnareff: Who the hell cares?
We’ll catch up soon anyway.

170
00:08:33,180 --> 00:08:34,948
- ( Car engine revs )
- Polnareff: That bastard!

171
00:08:34,982 --> 00:08:38,552
I’m gonna nail him
once we round this curve.

172
00:08:38,585 --> 00:08:39,986
( Gasps )

173
00:08:40,020 --> 00:08:41,955
A dead end! That’s impossible!

174
00:08:49,196 --> 00:08:51,165
Joseph: Where the hell’d he go?
He’s gone.

175
00:08:51,198 --> 00:08:53,967
Polnareff: Did he
just drive off the cliff?

176
00:08:54,001 --> 00:08:56,637
Kakyoin: There’s no way he could
cross the suspension bridge.

177
00:08:56,670 --> 00:08:58,805
- ( Crash )
- ( Car engine revs )

178
00:08:58,839 --> 00:09:00,174
Men: What?!

179
00:09:02,209 --> 00:09:03,644
( Anne gasps )

180
00:09:03,677 --> 00:09:05,679
Joseph: I-it’s him.
He keeps pushing us.

181
00:09:05,712 --> 00:09:08,248
Kakyoin: How the hell
did he get behind us?

182
00:09:08,282 --> 00:09:11,085
- ( Polnareff grunts )
- ( Tires squealing )

183
00:09:11,118 --> 00:09:14,688
Damn. How much horsepower is
that piece of junk running with?

184
00:09:14,721 --> 00:09:17,090
Damn it.
It’s like fighting a tank!

185
00:09:17,124 --> 00:09:19,126
( Engines revving )

186
00:09:20,127 --> 00:09:22,696
( Yells )

187
00:09:22,729 --> 00:09:24,264
It’s no use. Everyone, get out!

188
00:09:24,298 --> 00:09:25,666
It’s our only chance.

189
00:09:25,699 --> 00:09:27,100
Kakyoin: Polnareff,
what are you doing?!

190
00:09:27,134 --> 00:09:28,636
You can’t get out of the car

191
00:09:28,669 --> 00:09:30,137
until the rest of us
are clear first.

192
00:09:30,170 --> 00:09:31,672
You have to hold down the brake.

193
00:09:31,705 --> 00:09:33,574
Polnareff: Huh?

194
00:09:33,607 --> 00:09:34,908
S-s-sorry.

195
00:09:36,944 --> 00:09:39,814
( All yelling )

196
00:09:39,847 --> 00:09:41,816
( Driver chuckles )

197
00:09:41,849 --> 00:09:43,317
Kakyoin: Hierophant green!

198
00:09:44,618 --> 00:09:45,986
Joseph: Stop!

199
00:09:46,019 --> 00:09:47,754
Hierophant
isn’t nearly strong enough

200
00:09:47,788 --> 00:09:49,657
to support this kind of weight!

201
00:09:49,690 --> 00:09:51,192
You’ll be torn to shreds!

202
00:09:51,225 --> 00:09:54,161
Kakyoin: Mr. Joestar,
with all due respect,

203
00:09:54,194 --> 00:09:57,798
I am aware of my own abilities.
I am not a fool.

204
00:10:01,201 --> 00:10:03,303
Joseph: Ah, I get it.

205
00:10:03,337 --> 00:10:05,973
You used the car’s winch
instead of just brute strength.

206
00:10:06,006 --> 00:10:07,975
Jotaro: Heh. Not bad, kakyoin.

207
00:10:08,008 --> 00:10:10,010
I got a question for you.

208
00:10:10,043 --> 00:10:11,244
You like sumo?

209
00:10:13,647 --> 00:10:15,916
Especially deadlocks
at the edge of the ring?

210
00:10:15,949 --> 00:10:17,818
Star platinum: Ora!

211
00:10:17,851 --> 00:10:20,620
Jotaro: It’s exciting,
isn’t it?!

212
00:10:20,654 --> 00:10:22,189
Star platinum: Ora!

213
00:10:22,222 --> 00:10:24,324
♪

214
00:10:32,032 --> 00:10:33,166
( Both groan )

215
00:10:33,200 --> 00:10:35,736
Kakyoin: Yeah.
I’m a fan of sumo.

216
00:10:35,769 --> 00:10:37,137
But in sumo,

217
00:10:37,171 --> 00:10:39,940
it’s against the rules
to punch your opponent.

218
00:10:39,973 --> 00:10:41,107
Jotaro: Hmm.

219
00:10:47,948 --> 00:10:50,884
Suggests he used a stand attack.

220
00:10:50,918 --> 00:10:52,720
I think it’s safe to say

221
00:10:52,753 --> 00:10:55,489
he’s just some weirdo
with an ax to grind.

222
00:10:55,522 --> 00:10:58,558
Polnareff: Yeah, either way,
he’s a goner after that fall.

223
00:10:58,592 --> 00:11:00,928
Heh. I guess
what goes around comes around.

224
00:11:00,961 --> 00:11:04,665
Anne: Yeah, but I still wonder,
how did it get behind us?

225
00:11:04,698 --> 00:11:07,501
It was like watching a magician
or something.

226
00:11:07,534 --> 00:11:09,202
It’s so strange.

227
00:11:09,236 --> 00:11:10,904
( Radio static )

228
00:11:10,938 --> 00:11:13,808
Man: Actually, little girl,
it’s not strange at all.

229
00:11:13,841 --> 00:11:15,009
( All gasp )

230
00:11:15,042 --> 00:11:16,110
Polnareff: The radio!

231
00:11:16,143 --> 00:11:18,212
He’s coming through the am-fm.

232
00:11:18,245 --> 00:11:22,683
Man: I was able to do that,
because it’s my stand, joestar.

233
00:11:22,716 --> 00:11:24,117
Joseph: What?!

234
00:11:24,151 --> 00:11:26,253
He knows my name,
so that confirms it.

235
00:11:26,286 --> 00:11:27,788
He’s an enemy stand user.

236
00:11:27,821 --> 00:11:28,922
Kakyoin: Where is he?

237
00:11:28,956 --> 00:11:30,558
Could he really be
sending a signal

238
00:11:30,591 --> 00:11:32,259
- from the car down there?
- Polnareff: No way!

239
00:11:32,292 --> 00:11:33,927
Do you see
the wreck down there?!

240
00:11:33,961 --> 00:11:38,499
Jotaro: No. That old jalopy
could very well be a stand.

241
00:11:38,532 --> 00:11:40,634
You remember the boat stand?

242
00:11:40,667 --> 00:11:42,235
This may be a repeat.

243
00:11:42,269 --> 00:11:44,671
Stand user:
Behold the wheel of fortune.

244
00:11:44,705 --> 00:11:47,841
My stand will lead you
to your maker.

245
00:11:47,875 --> 00:11:50,211
Joseph: The wheel of fortune?

246
00:11:50,244 --> 00:11:51,545
( Rumbling )

247
00:11:51,578 --> 00:11:52,979
Kakyoin: What the--
an earthquake?

248
00:11:53,013 --> 00:11:54,681
Polnareff:
I’ve got a bad feeling.

249
00:11:54,715 --> 00:11:56,183
Joseph: Everybody,
get in the car!

250
00:11:56,216 --> 00:11:58,952
Jotaro: No! Stay back!
Don’t go anywhere near it!

251
00:11:58,986 --> 00:11:59,954
Polnareff: Couldn’t be.

252
00:11:59,987 --> 00:12:01,755
Below us!

253
00:12:01,788 --> 00:12:03,757
( All yelling )

254
00:12:09,730 --> 00:12:11,832
( All groan )

255
00:12:11,865 --> 00:12:13,166
♪

256
00:12:13,200 --> 00:12:14,301
Polnareff: Impossible!

257
00:12:14,334 --> 00:12:16,236
It burrowed up
through the ground!

258
00:12:16,270 --> 00:12:18,806
All right,
I think it’s pretty obvious

259
00:12:18,839 --> 00:12:20,541
that car is actually a stand.

260
00:12:20,574 --> 00:12:23,644
Kakyoin: Looks like the stand’s
user is inside the car.

261
00:12:26,613 --> 00:12:28,582
Polnareff: What the hell?!

262
00:12:30,617 --> 00:12:32,319
Kakyoin: Now what is it doing?

263
00:12:36,089 --> 00:12:37,591
Joseph: It’s like it’s alive!

264
00:12:37,624 --> 00:12:40,026
( Engine revving )

265
00:12:44,364 --> 00:12:47,033
Polnareff: It’s heading
straight for us!

266
00:12:49,703 --> 00:12:51,071
( Jotaro chuckles )

267
00:12:51,104 --> 00:12:53,640
If it’s a duel you want,
i’m happy to oblige.

268
00:12:53,674 --> 00:12:56,210
Joseph: Don’t do it, jotaro!
Don’t fight it yet,

269
00:12:56,243 --> 00:12:58,712
not until we know
what that stand’s power is!

270
00:13:00,047 --> 00:13:01,982
( Jotaro grunts )

271
00:13:02,015 --> 00:13:03,917
- ( Gags )
- Men: Jotaro!

272
00:13:03,951 --> 00:13:06,687
Jotaro: Impossible.
I couldn’t see it.

273
00:13:06,720 --> 00:13:08,322
What the hell
did he shoot at me,

274
00:13:08,355 --> 00:13:09,923
and how the hell did he--

275
00:13:09,957 --> 00:13:11,125
( stand user laughs )

276
00:13:11,158 --> 00:13:13,594
Don’t even know
what hit you, eh?

277
00:13:13,627 --> 00:13:14,795
( Laughs )

278
00:13:14,828 --> 00:13:16,763
You’ll soon find out,

279
00:13:16,797 --> 00:13:20,000
the moment you croak, that is!

280
00:13:21,134 --> 00:13:22,335
Kakyoin: Jotaro!

281
00:13:22,369 --> 00:13:23,804
( All groan )

282
00:13:23,837 --> 00:13:26,640
Joseph: Jotaro!
Polnareff! Kakyoin!

283
00:13:26,673 --> 00:13:27,807
( Anne screams )

284
00:13:30,110 --> 00:13:32,079
( Polnareff gags )
Damn! What the hell is this?

285
00:13:32,112 --> 00:13:34,281
The wounds aren’t deep,
but they sting like hell!

286
00:13:34,314 --> 00:13:35,982
Kakyoin: I can’t see it at all.

287
00:13:36,016 --> 00:13:37,851
I thought the car
threw something at us,

288
00:13:37,885 --> 00:13:39,186
but there’s nothing
inside our wounds.

289
00:13:39,219 --> 00:13:41,088
What the hell is going on here?!

290
00:13:41,121 --> 00:13:43,156
Joseph: Jotaro,
are you all right?

291
00:13:43,190 --> 00:13:45,893
Jotaro: Don’t worry about me,
old man.

292
00:13:47,127 --> 00:13:48,762
I don’t know what the hell

293
00:13:48,795 --> 00:13:50,664
he’s hurling at us,
but he’s got damn good aim.

294
00:13:50,697 --> 00:13:52,832
Stand user:
I’ll pulverize your legs

295
00:13:52,866 --> 00:13:56,269
so you can’t move
and then run you over!

296
00:13:56,303 --> 00:13:59,006
Joseph: Everyone,
run between the boulders!

297
00:14:01,808 --> 00:14:04,778
Stand user:
Stop running away, you cowards!

298
00:14:04,811 --> 00:14:06,913
- Kakyoin: What?
- Stand user: What are you?

299
00:14:06,947 --> 00:14:07,948
Roaches?

300
00:14:09,349 --> 00:14:11,751
Joseph: Oh, no!
He’s digging his way through!

301
00:14:11,785 --> 00:14:13,887
Kakyoin: And we’re
no match for him in here.

302
00:14:13,921 --> 00:14:15,222
Polnareff: What a freak.

303
00:14:15,255 --> 00:14:16,990
He’s acting like
some stupid musclehead

304
00:14:17,024 --> 00:14:20,127
who got cut off in traffic and
flew into a fit of road rage.

305
00:14:20,160 --> 00:14:21,695
Jotaro: Just keep running.

306
00:14:25,899 --> 00:14:27,267
( Anne gasps )

307
00:14:27,301 --> 00:14:29,870
Wait! Come back!
I can’t keep up!

308
00:14:29,903 --> 00:14:31,304
( Screams )

309
00:14:31,338 --> 00:14:34,241
Yeah, okay,
so I ran away from home!

310
00:14:34,274 --> 00:14:37,677
I’m a good-for-nothing drifter
that nobody loves!

311
00:14:37,711 --> 00:14:39,313
I’m gonna die!

312
00:14:40,314 --> 00:14:41,782
Jotaro: Good grief.

313
00:14:41,815 --> 00:14:44,051
If you have time
to say all that crap,

314
00:14:44,084 --> 00:14:46,286
you can run away,
you damn little brat.

315
00:14:46,320 --> 00:14:49,156
Anne: I love you
so much, jotaro!

316
00:14:49,189 --> 00:14:51,191
( Sobbing )

317
00:14:53,493 --> 00:14:55,895
( Stand user laughs )

318
00:14:55,929 --> 00:14:57,798
Go ahead and climb.

319
00:14:57,831 --> 00:15:00,267
There’s no path left
for you to take,

320
00:15:00,300 --> 00:15:03,003
no way to escape,
no way to survive,

321
00:15:03,036 --> 00:15:06,706
and, last but certainly
not least, no future!

322
00:15:06,740 --> 00:15:08,909
Because this wheel of fortune

323
00:15:08,942 --> 00:15:11,778
is going to grind you
into mincemeat

324
00:15:11,812 --> 00:15:14,748
and splatter you
all over these boulders!

325
00:15:14,781 --> 00:15:18,151
I’ll paint this mountain red
with your guts!

326
00:15:18,185 --> 00:15:19,820
Jotaro: Hmm.

327
00:15:19,853 --> 00:15:21,221
Joseph: Oh, no!

328
00:15:21,255 --> 00:15:22,890
Kakyoin: It’s climbing
up the cliff.

329
00:15:22,923 --> 00:15:25,392
Polnareff: Is there
anything this car can’t do?

330
00:15:27,327 --> 00:15:28,995
Jotaro: Ah, good grief.

331
00:15:29,029 --> 00:15:31,331
Looks like the time
to fight him’s now.

332
00:15:31,365 --> 00:15:33,868
The rest of you, stay back.
He’s mine.

333
00:15:33,901 --> 00:15:36,904
Once he climbs up here,
the car’s underside’ll be bare.

334
00:15:36,937 --> 00:15:40,908
Then we’ll see
just how strong this thing is.

335
00:15:40,941 --> 00:15:42,209
Kakyoin: I get it.

336
00:15:42,242 --> 00:15:43,510
Once its underside’s exposed,

337
00:15:43,544 --> 00:15:45,379
we may be able to attack it.

338
00:15:45,412 --> 00:15:47,514
( Rocks crunching )

339
00:15:51,451 --> 00:15:53,186
( Jotaro yells )

340
00:15:53,220 --> 00:15:54,888
( Stand user laughs )

341
00:15:54,922 --> 00:15:58,192
You’re pretty fast there,
jotaro, but not too bright.

342
00:15:58,225 --> 00:15:59,793
( Jotaro yells )

343
00:15:59,826 --> 00:16:01,161
Stand user: Your bodies reek,

344
00:16:01,195 --> 00:16:02,763
and you haven’t even noticed.

345
00:16:02,796 --> 00:16:04,398
Try paying attention!

346
00:16:04,431 --> 00:16:05,499
( Jotaro gasps )

347
00:16:05,532 --> 00:16:07,134
Kakyoin: Come to think of it,

348
00:16:07,167 --> 00:16:08,802
I guess I did smell gasoline.

349
00:16:08,836 --> 00:16:09,837
( Polnareff sniffs )

350
00:16:09,870 --> 00:16:12,339
Oh, no. It’s coming from us.

351
00:16:12,372 --> 00:16:14,207
Our bodies smell
like a gas station.

352
00:16:17,845 --> 00:16:21,215
Kakyoin: That’s what
it was shooting, gasoline.

353
00:16:21,248 --> 00:16:23,417
It was shooting
small amounts of it

354
00:16:23,450 --> 00:16:26,119
at high speed like bullets.
Incredible.

355
00:16:26,153 --> 00:16:27,388
Polnareff: This is nuts!

356
00:16:27,421 --> 00:16:29,423
So he wasn’t trying to wound us.

357
00:16:29,456 --> 00:16:31,391
He was dousing our bodies
with gasoline.

358
00:16:31,425 --> 00:16:32,960
We’re covered in the stuff!

359
00:16:32,993 --> 00:16:34,294
( Jotaro groans )

360
00:16:34,328 --> 00:16:36,997
Stand user: Looks like
you finally caught on,

361
00:16:37,030 --> 00:16:38,798
but it’s too late now.

362
00:16:38,832 --> 00:16:41,101
Now all you need
is a little jolt.

363
00:16:44,505 --> 00:16:46,807
Jotaro: What?!

364
00:16:46,840 --> 00:16:48,842
- ( Men gasp )
- ( Anne screams )

365
00:16:48,876 --> 00:16:50,411
Jotaro!

366
00:16:50,444 --> 00:16:52,413
( Jotaro screaming )

367
00:16:55,449 --> 00:16:56,817
Joseph: Jotaro!

368
00:16:56,850 --> 00:16:58,885
Kakyoin: Mr. Joestar, stay back!

369
00:16:58,919 --> 00:17:00,421
We’re soaking
with gasoline, too.

370
00:17:00,454 --> 00:17:01,422
It’s too dangerous.

371
00:17:01,455 --> 00:17:04,425
( Stand user laughs )

372
00:17:07,060 --> 00:17:08,929
Joseph: Jotaro!

373
00:17:08,962 --> 00:17:10,997
Stand user: I win.

374
00:17:11,031 --> 00:17:14,101
Your Valiant hero
finally bit the dust.

375
00:17:14,134 --> 00:17:17,504
( Laughing )

376
00:17:21,141 --> 00:17:22,876
Jotaro: Is that so?

377
00:17:22,910 --> 00:17:26,180
And who exactly
would replace me, jotaro kujo?

378
00:17:26,213 --> 00:17:27,214
( Stand user gasps )

379
00:17:28,649 --> 00:17:29,917
Huh?!

380
00:17:29,950 --> 00:17:32,219
♪

381
00:17:33,253 --> 00:17:34,488
Jotaro: Let me guess.

382
00:17:34,521 --> 00:17:36,623
You thought it’d be you,
you road-hog?

383
00:17:36,657 --> 00:17:38,192
( Stand user gasps )

384
00:17:38,225 --> 00:17:40,494
You burrowed into the ground
with star platinum,

385
00:17:40,527 --> 00:17:43,163
so the only thing
that burned up was your jacket!

386
00:17:43,197 --> 00:17:44,498
( Jotaro scoffs )

387
00:17:44,531 --> 00:17:46,199
A little parting wisdom.

388
00:17:46,233 --> 00:17:48,869
What you said earlier
about paths...

389
00:17:48,902 --> 00:17:50,303
Was dead wrong.

390
00:17:50,337 --> 00:17:54,041
You see, in life,
you have to forge your own path.

391
00:17:54,074 --> 00:17:55,909
No one can do it for you.

392
00:17:55,943 --> 00:17:57,378
So i’ll offer you some guidance.

393
00:17:58,512 --> 00:18:00,180
( Stand user whimpers )

394
00:18:00,214 --> 00:18:03,050
Jotaro: But first you have
to go through a little pain.

395
00:18:03,083 --> 00:18:06,019
( Star platinum yelling )

396
00:18:09,423 --> 00:18:11,392
Stand user: I-i’m being crushed.

397
00:18:11,425 --> 00:18:12,559
Anne: Go, jotaro!

398
00:18:12,593 --> 00:18:15,563
( Star platinum yelling )

399
00:18:15,596 --> 00:18:16,564
Ora!

400
00:18:16,597 --> 00:18:18,999
( Stand user yells )

401
00:18:24,037 --> 00:18:26,573
Jotaro: That is how it’s done.

402
00:18:26,607 --> 00:18:28,909
See? You just paved
your own path.

403
00:18:28,942 --> 00:18:31,011
Congrats on being
a fast learner.

404
00:18:31,044 --> 00:18:32,479
Here ends the lesson.

405
00:18:32,513 --> 00:18:36,050
♪

406
00:18:37,985 --> 00:18:39,587
( Stand user screams )

407
00:18:39,620 --> 00:18:41,288
Kakyoin: What an odd guy.

408
00:18:41,321 --> 00:18:43,523
His arms are
the size of boulders,

409
00:18:43,557 --> 00:18:45,993
and yet everything else
is so small.

410
00:18:46,026 --> 00:18:47,995
Talk about a bluff.

411
00:18:48,028 --> 00:18:50,931
( Stand user whimpering )

412
00:18:50,964 --> 00:18:52,065
( Screams )

413
00:18:52,099 --> 00:18:54,401
Polnareff: Hello.
Going somewhere?

414
00:18:56,436 --> 00:18:58,338
Stand user: Please,
don’t kill me.

415
00:18:58,372 --> 00:19:01,008
I’m just in this
for the money, honest.

416
00:19:01,041 --> 00:19:03,410
( All laughing )

417
00:19:03,443 --> 00:19:04,945
( Wheel of fortune squeaking )

418
00:19:04,978 --> 00:19:05,979
All: Huh?

419
00:19:15,022 --> 00:19:16,524
Joseph: Oh,
would you look at that?

420
00:19:16,557 --> 00:19:18,459
I can’t believe
the stand was disguising

421
00:19:18,492 --> 00:19:20,427
such a small car
that entire time.

422
00:19:20,460 --> 00:19:22,629
Kinda reminds me
of a fluffy little sheep

423
00:19:22,663 --> 00:19:24,999
that just had
all of its wool shorn off.

424
00:19:25,032 --> 00:19:27,001
( Sheep bleats )

425
00:19:27,034 --> 00:19:29,303
What a pathetic hunk of junk.

426
00:19:29,336 --> 00:19:31,338
( All laughing )

427
00:19:35,042 --> 00:19:37,044
( Stand user gasping )

428
00:19:42,049 --> 00:19:44,385
Joseph: Well, then, let’s take
his car across the border.

429
00:19:44,418 --> 00:19:47,021
Only fair,
since he smashed ours.

430
00:19:47,054 --> 00:19:48,556
Kakyoin:
It’s pretty beat-up, though.

431
00:19:48,589 --> 00:19:50,724
I wonder
if it’ll last that long.

432
00:19:50,757 --> 00:19:53,026
Stand user: Help! Help!

433
00:19:53,060 --> 00:19:55,195
Jotaro: And you’re
on the next flight to Hong Kong

434
00:19:55,229 --> 00:19:56,297
once we find an airport.

435
00:19:56,330 --> 00:19:57,331
Anne: Aw, no! Why?!

436
00:19:57,364 --> 00:19:59,199
Polnareff: Shut up!

437
00:19:59,233 --> 00:20:01,402
Don’t you understand that you’re
in the way, you little brat?

438
00:20:01,435 --> 00:20:02,636
( Car clunks )

439
00:20:02,669 --> 00:20:05,539
Joseph: Uh, we might
not make it that far.

440
00:20:05,572 --> 00:20:08,275
Stand user: Help!

441
00:20:08,609 --> 00:20:10,611
( Enyaba sobbing )

442
00:20:17,084 --> 00:20:19,086
( Sobbing continues )

443
00:20:22,089 --> 00:20:27,261
My seven assassins have all
been defeated, and so easily.

444
00:20:27,294 --> 00:20:30,564
How could they
be crushed like that?

445
00:20:30,597 --> 00:20:31,998
The shame!

446
00:20:32,032 --> 00:20:34,768
I cannot bear to face lord dio.

447
00:20:34,801 --> 00:20:36,770
( Wails )

448
00:20:36,803 --> 00:20:39,039
Damn you! Curse you, polnareff!

449
00:20:39,072 --> 00:20:40,340
Curse kakyoin!

450
00:20:40,374 --> 00:20:43,611
Curse jotaro
and his wretched grandfather.

451
00:20:43,644 --> 00:20:46,780
( Screams )

452
00:20:46,813 --> 00:20:51,284
I, enyaba, shall be
your next and final opponent!

453
00:20:51,318 --> 00:20:54,021
I will fight
with my very own stand,

454
00:20:54,054 --> 00:20:56,290
the stand of justice!

455
00:20:59,826 --> 00:21:01,828
♪

456
00:21:13,640 --> 00:21:16,276
♪ All the old paintings
on the tomb ♪

457
00:21:16,310 --> 00:21:18,546
♪ they do the sand dance,
don’t you know ♪

458
00:21:18,579 --> 00:21:19,680
♪ if they move too quick

459
00:21:19,713 --> 00:21:21,248
♪ oh, whey, oh

460
00:21:21,281 --> 00:21:23,216
♪ they’re falling down
like a domino ♪

461
00:21:23,250 --> 00:21:25,552
♪ all the bazaar men
by the nile ♪

462
00:21:25,586 --> 00:21:27,655
♪ they got the money on a bet

463
00:21:27,688 --> 00:21:29,056
♪ gold crocodiles

464
00:21:29,089 --> 00:21:30,390
♪ oh, whey, oh

465
00:21:30,424 --> 00:21:32,459
♪ they snap their teeth
on your cigarette ♪

466
00:21:32,492 --> 00:21:34,594
♪ foreign types
with the hookah pipes say ♪

467
00:21:34,628 --> 00:21:37,064
♪ whey, oh, whey, oh

468
00:21:37,097 --> 00:21:40,601
♪ ay, whey, oh, whey, oh

469
00:21:41,702 --> 00:21:44,338
♪ walk like an Egyptian

470
00:21:55,415 --> 00:21:58,285
♪ The blond waitresses
take their trays ♪

471
00:21:58,318 --> 00:22:00,387
♪ they spin around,
and they cross the floor ♪

472
00:22:00,420 --> 00:22:01,655
♪ they’ve got the moves

473
00:22:01,688 --> 00:22:02,656
♪ oh, whey, oh

474
00:22:02,689 --> 00:22:03,690
♪ you drop your drink

475
00:22:03,724 --> 00:22:05,192
♪ then they bring you more

476
00:22:05,225 --> 00:22:07,461
♪ all the school kids
so sick of books ♪

477
00:22:07,494 --> 00:22:09,663
♪ they like the punk
and the metal band ♪

478
00:22:09,696 --> 00:22:11,097
♪ when the buzzer rings

479
00:22:11,131 --> 00:22:12,399
♪ oh, whey, oh

480
00:22:12,432 --> 00:22:14,401
♪ they’re walking
like an Egyptian ♪

481
00:22:14,434 --> 00:22:16,536
♪ all the kids
in the marketplace say ♪

482
00:22:16,570 --> 00:22:18,772
♪ whey, oh, whey, oh

483
00:22:18,805 --> 00:22:23,576
♪ ay, whey, oh, whey, oh

484
00:22:23,610 --> 00:22:26,680
♪ walk like an Egyptian

